star💫 2023-10-26 6:47 PM
of course!! it’s a 1/2 cup of brown sugar, 1/2 cup of white sugar, and 1/2 cup of butter mixed with a hand mixer for a couple minutes until it’s all creamed together. then added a 1/2 cup of peanut butter, an egg, and a couple teaspoons of vanilla and mixy mixed that. then in a different bowl added 1 cup of flour and 1 1/4 cups of old fashioned rolled oats (i put half of the oats in the blender for like one spin so it would have less texture, it doesn’t take much spin), 1/2 teaspoon baking soda, 1/2 teaspoon baking powder, and about 1/4 teaspoon salt. mixed those then added them to my wet stuff and hand mixer’d it again. add however many mnms and chocolate chips your heart desires… i added like 2 cups of mnms and 1 cup of chocolate chips. then baked them for 10ish minutes at 350 on a sheet lined with parchment paper. very yum :3
